File: Graeme Smith. Brenton Geach / AFP JOHANNESBURG - Cricket South Africa's former Director of Cricket, Graeme Smith, has been cleared of racism. Two independent arbitrators were called in to investigate the claims, which emanated from CSA's Social Justice and Nation-Building process. They have found no evidence to prove Smith racially discriminated against Thami Tsolekile. READ:Â Smith rejects charges of racism The arbitrators also say they cannot conclude that he is racially biased against black leadership at CSA. And they say they canot conclude that Mark Boucher's appointment as coach was unfair racial discrimination. Cricket South Africa has been ordered to pay Smith's legal costs.